You can already run <i>some</i> CPAN modules in Rakudo (Perl 6) on Parrot.   See Blizkost (which comes with Rakudo): <a href="https://github.com/jnthn/blizkost" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/jnthn/blizkost</a><p>Here is an example which works (using CGI module from perl5/CPAN):<p><pre><code>    use v6;
    use CGI:from<perl5>;

    my $q = CGI.new;
    print $q.header,
        $q.start_html('Hello World'),
        $q.h1('Hello World'),
        $q.end_html;
</code></pre>
PS. re: <i>some</i> CPAN modules - Only "well behaved" Perl5 modules will work.  I've tried four and got one to work.  However this is a good start methinks!
